"script": "If you saw how a hot dog begins, you might never eat one again. First, leftover scraps of meat are dumped into a giant grinder and blended with ice and seasoning. Then the machine spins so fast the meat turns into a smooth pink paste they actually call batter. And this paste is squirted into long thin tubes, sometimes made from cleaned animal intestines. Next, they're smoked and cooked until firm, and the casings are peeled off in seconds. Finally, they're packed and shipped, and almost nobody guesses their juicy hot dog started life as a slurry.",
